task.summary: Default task
Added experimental GNU GPL Tinker 3D Library
End of day changes 2019-09-23
Added proper background image support, rotation, calibration, and a little UI
Began work on mouse support. Not complete, but in the works. Fixed rotation.
Garrick meeting changes. Added ability to change size of Boxes
Shifted focus to OpenGL development and away from Vpython due to limitations. Hope this is a good idea!
Everything is a complete mess why did I do this to myself
Added translation and modification of bounding boxes with keyboard controls. (see pygame inputs at bottom for instruction)

Improved controls with macro and fine adjustment. Began work on rotation (still suspect, I likely messed up the trig). Added ability to delete bounding boxes (which throws an out of bounds exception in common cases, needs work).
Fixed rotation. Improved visualization and blink timing when swithcing boxes. Fixed obscure oob errors. Began work on image shaders.
Added background image cobbled together with sample code and prayers. It works. I think I sacrificed my soul in the process.

Added text display using GLUT for Bounding Box labels.
There were some issues with the Python default GLUT install, so you may have to install some .wpl files from this website (at least that fixed it for me). https://python-catalin.blogspot.com/2018/08/pyopengl-fix-attempt-to-call-undefined.html
GLUT changes and ALT changes.
GLUT changes and ALT changes.
Added simplified Pygame OpenGL code.
Mid-day opengl pushes for James debugging.
Added camera controls and calibrated grid for 1 meter units.
Added instructions, default sizes, and types. The code is still very messy, but we will work on splitting it soon.
Changed test image
Split opengl_pygame into several classes and generally cleaned up the code.
Split main into render(visualisation) and main(data). Allowed for background image to be updated. Allowed for arbitrary numbers of objects.
